<h3 class="tool_heading">Memo for Middle/High School Families</h3>
<p><meta charset="utf-8"></p>
<p dir="ltr">Update April 17, 2020</p>
<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-af5638e9-7fff-ba5d-6097-16c5c8591ac4">Hi Beaver Families,</b></p>
<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-af5638e9-7fff-ba5d-6097-16c5c8591ac4">I hope all is well as we are settling into online learning.  By now you know the news of the “Safer at Home” order being extended, thus shutting down in-person schooling for the remainder of the year.  I know this is sad news for many, especially our Seniors. While this is less than ideal, we will continue to do the best we can to provide education for your student(s).  While the school year will not resume in-person, we still expect students to engage in online learning with their teachers through Friday, May 29th, which will be the last day of school.  The following week, students will be allowed back in the building to clean their lockers and return technology and textbooks.  More information on that will be coming. We will also be communicating more information out regarding summer school, graduation, senior awards and recognitions, etc.  I will need time to decide how to proceed in these areas.  </b></p>
<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-af5638e9-7fff-ba5d-6097-16c5c8591ac4">Below is a list of the expectations that I have for our students and staff for the remainder of the year.  Please look this over so you and your student(s) understands the district’s expectation for passing. If you have any concerns about a class, please contact that teacher.</b></p>
<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-af5638e9-7fff-ba5d-6097-16c5c8591ac4">I know this is difficult, I know it is stressful, and I know this is less than desirable.  I simply ask that your student(s) does the best they can to remain engaged in learning. Please stay healthy and safe, and as always, if you need anything at all, please let me know.  Take care,</b></p>
<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-af5638e9-7fff-ba5d-6097-16c5c8591ac4">Reed</b></p>
<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-af5638e9-7fff-ba5d-6097-16c5c8591ac4">As we prepare to be homebound for the remainder of the school year, here are the expectations:</b></p>
<ul>
<li dir="ltr">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><b id="docs-internal-guid-af5638e9-7fff-ba5d-6097-16c5c8591ac4">The third quarter grading window will close on Friday, May 1st.  All students will need to have submitted missing work or improved their grade by that date.  </b></p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><b id="docs-internal-guid-af5638e9-7fff-ba5d-6097-16c5c8591ac4">Starting on Monday, May 4th, new learning concepts will be taught for the remainder of the school year.  I understand that we will not be able to teach these concepts as thoroughly as we would as if we were in person, but we will support students through this process.</b></p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><b id="docs-internal-guid-af5638e9-7fff-ba5d-6097-16c5c8591ac4">Grading for fourth quarter will be “pass/fail” based on participation and effort.  Even though we are introducing new concepts, students will not be graded, rather, feedback will be given to support students.  I realize this may look different in each class or subject, so I will not put a “blanket expectation” out as to what constitutes a “pass/fail”.  Teachers will have the autonomy to decide that based on their interactions with their students. The only thing I ask is that those expectations are communicated to the students and their families.</b></p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><b id="docs-internal-guid-af5638e9-7fff-ba5d-6097-16c5c8591ac4">My expectations for semester grades will not change from what I have communicated out from the start.  The semester grade will be a combination of the third quarter grade and if a student participated, showed effort, remained engaged, etc. in learning during fourth quarter.  If students are trying, they will pass. </b></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1nWRFRbXlfEQCYSDhjbU30xUJB4JRE_kzcUHFclLLD3w/edit?usp=sharing">April 2, 2020 Update </a></p>
<p> </p>
</td></tr>
