<h3 class="tool_heading">Memo for Elementary Families</h3>
<p><meta charset="utf-8"></p>
<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-56c4f1b3-7fff-fa9e-3cac-6fc5c88a12ac">Updated April 17, 2020 </b></p>
<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-56c4f1b3-7fff-fa9e-3cac-6fc5c88a12ac">Dear Families of an Augusta Elementary Student,</b></p>
<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-56c4f1b3-7fff-fa9e-3cac-6fc5c88a12ac">I hope this email finds all of you healthy and adjusting well to this difficult situation. Please know that we are thinking about all of you during this unprecedented time.</b></p>
<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-56c4f1b3-7fff-fa9e-3cac-6fc5c88a12ac">Yesterday, Governor Tony Evers announced that all schools in the state of Wisconsin will remain closed through the end of the school year. Our teachers and staff have been planning for this possibility and are ready to continue delivering essential instruction virtually or through packet-based materials from now through May 26. Up until this point our teachers have been engaging students without trying to overwhelm them with new instruction.  With that being said, we feel in order to keep our students engaged we will slowly incorporate new learning concepts starting the first week of May through the remainder of the school year. The expectation is that all of our students be engaged in the learning provided by their teacher each week. Help your child the best you can, when you can.  Based on the level of your child’s engagement will determine if your child receives a satisfactory or non-satisfactory score for the third trimester.  Therefore, it is very important that students continue to be engaged.</b></p>
<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-56c4f1b3-7fff-fa9e-3cac-6fc5c88a12ac">With that, I want to thank you and your family for your patience, understanding, and flexibility during this unprecedented time. The pandemic has caused considerable disruptions to our daily lives. Let’s continue to work together to support each other, looking forward to that time when life returns to normal in Augusta and across the world. </b></p>
<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-56c4f1b3-7fff-fa9e-3cac-6fc5c88a12ac">Your Partner in Education,</b></p>
<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-56c4f1b3-7fff-fa9e-3cac-6fc5c88a12ac">Mrs. Steinmetz</b></p>
<p dir="ltr"> </p>
<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Ng_Uo4Ltf2HXsu4ez5MOhhwS50sJlbf8HoEtVkkoGdo/edit?usp=sharing">April 1, 2020 update </a></p>
<p> </p>
</td></tr>
